{
  "texts": [
    "Formally, given a sequence of latent states Z 0:L-1 = (Z 0,.",
    ", Z L-1), the transformer produces the dynamic context representation for time step t:",
    ", where Z BOS is a learned begin-of-sequence (BOS) token.",
    "Z L DYN can be seen as a latent context capturing the dynamics, from the observed time-steps [0, L -1], to predict the next step L.",
    "To support parallel training and efficient inference, this factorization is implemented using a blockwise causal attention mask (see Appendix D)."
  ]
}